This man doesn't deserve all the hate he's getting since last year, so let us protect him. I'm also glad that he's completely fine and that's what really matters the most to me.

Please send our appreciation not just for him but for the whole group because they deserve the recognition they're getting right now. Fighting!

author: @sundaymorningrainisfalling
text:
Happy Birthday you beautiful Angel!! Many many returns of this special day.
You'll always have a special place in my heart as you were the one who got my attention first. You drew me into Seventeen and I'll forever be thankful for that. I'll always remember how in the interview with Sakshma di you specially thanked her for asking good meaningful questions. It struck me how thoughtful  you were. You didn't have to go out of your way to thank her, but you did because that's how you are. The epitome of Grace, Charm and Mannerism.
Please always be your calm, caring, gentle and sometimes crazy-weird self. 
We love you so much Shuaa!! Always praying for your Happiness, Health, Success and Prosperity.
Keep shining, keep growing. Carats wish you the best as always<333

author: @joshuastarwalker
text:
In the original version, all I could feel is the sadness.
But with Shua's version, he added something into the song, so now it's beautiful and sad, at the same time. The way his voice is cracked in the part of 'In the midst of the crowds - In the shapes in the clouds' really got me. It's like a burst of emotions when he has to confess everything. Shua's singing this song his own way, he understands the song and the feeling of the song like it's his own story (or is it also his own story too, I wonder?). Really nice and touching. The original got me the feeling of broken and deep sad, and Shua gave me a gentle sadness,  it's still a painful feeling but he kept it inside and expressed it bit by bit, elegantly and sadly, that's like the way he always be. Really love this cover and thanks to dhruv for this song too <3

author: @vindicatedtruth
text:
If thereâ€™s one thing Iâ€™m glad Pledis is able to do for SEVENTEEN, itâ€™s that all the members are allowed to explore solo works and projects as much as they can in between their hectic group releases.

Itâ€™s rare for a groupâ€”with 13 members at thatâ€”to be able to shine on their own individually together with being a group, but SEVENTEEN has always been that precious rarity in Kpop in which they have such all-encompassing creative freedom to do what they want both as a group and as individual artistsâ€”and with the matching talent to boot.

Thatâ€™s exactly what makes SEVENTEEN so special: they are less a group with 13 members, and more of 13 incredibly talented solo artists who just happened to debut together.

And itâ€™s such an honor to watch all 13 of them shine in their own light.
